  "_doc": "Curated EPSG round-trip control points. Each fixture verifies that the bundled proj4 string for a projected CRS round-trips a published (projected → WGS84 → projected) coordinate within tolerance_m metres, AND that the forward output stays within tolerance_m of the captured baseline lat/lon. Used by scripts/verify-epsg-roundtrip.ts to catch regressions when the bundled EPSG index is regenerated. The expected_wgs84 values are the proj4 output produced by the *current* bundled definitions (post-sanitization for grid-file CRSs); they become a regression baseline. Add a fixture for every CRS family that real users have hit problems with. Tolerances reflect proj4js's browser-side accuracy without grid files: ~1-5m for ETRS89/WGS84 lineages, ~5-10m for Bessel-based national grids relying on +towgs84.",
